For the `remove` case, I'll add the recursive flag and check directories. There are a few details to clarify about handling URLs and dates, particularly for commands involving repositories.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Feature in Arguments**\\n\\nI'm considering whether the `getArguments()` method should include \\\"feature\\\" as part of its functionality. This could enhance how features are handled in the command. I need to clarify how this fits into the overall context and ensure that it aligns with any existing processes. It's important to think about how adding \\\"feature\\\" will impact the functionality and usability of the command. I'll keep this in mind as I move forward!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing consumer lines**\\n\\nI need to differentiate consumer lines and split a raw format by whitespace into six parts. For example, from \\\":000000 100644 0000000 e69de29 A\\\\tnew.txt\\\", I can split it correctly into components: [\\\":000000\\\", \\\"100644\\\", \\\"0000000\\\", \\\"e69de29\\\", \\\"A\\\", \\\"new.txt\\\"]. That's good. Now, I should focus on remote info, especially regarding branches and tag maps, to keep everything organized. I also want to ensure I’m checking the latest revision properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2ciCU9ZGpZOJMsfgiNcEFLJC|fc_0cfb9b676d54242a016a01e77814f881948c62e798a82bee1b", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/tmp/gitexe-src/org/apache/maven/scm/provider/git/gitexe/command/update/GitLatestRevisionCommandConsumer.java", "limit": 90}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1103, "output": 943, "cacheRead": 51712, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53758, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778509671604, "responseId": "resp_0cfb9b676d54242a016a01e76832788194b9f3736c79d8767b"}}
